name: Compound Novice
Contents:
That's all well and good, you ask, but how can I make money with it?

In 2019, Novartis paid $10B to acquire The Medicines Company. Their only asset: Inclisiran, an investigative RNAi drug to lower cholesterol.

$10B for one drug candidate! That shows the potential value here.

name: Sam Tsimikas, MD
Contents: 6/20 The first PCSK9i to lower LDL-C were antibodies that lower LDL-C ~60%, then siRNA inclisiran ~50%, and latest is @ionispharma  (AZD8233 with AZ) antisense that lowers LDL-C 70%. Inclisiran and AZD8233 are not approved yet in US.

I disagree as you pigeon hole this!
